WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.940 --> 00:00:15.080
Pardon me.

2
00:00:15.740 --> 00:00:19.750
Hi! Sorry. I didn't see you there.

3
00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:22.450
Oh. no. no. please never apologize for a kiss. signora.

4
00:00:22.590 --> 00:00:24.500
Especially for one like that

5
00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:29.360
'95 brunello di montalcino.

6
00:00:29.960 --> 00:00:31.890
Great. Decant it. please?

7
00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:33.030
Of course.

8
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:36.470
Oh. wow. Was that embarrassing.

9
00:00:36.770 --> 00:00:39.030
You heard what the man said. Never apologize.

10
00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:41.570
I'm so happy for you.

11
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:43.110
I still can't believe it.

12
00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:46.840
Phoebe. I've wanted to buy my granddad's winery ever since he lost it.

13
00:00:48.410 --> 00:00:50.710
I just hope he knows that somehow.

14
00:00:51.610 --> 00:00:52.720
Believe me. he does.

15
00:00:53.550 --> 00:00:55.680
You talk as if you have inside information.

16
00:00:56.150 --> 00:00:57.220
Well. maybe I do.

17
00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:02.960
You are special. Phoebe.

18
00:01:07.130 --> 00:01:08.800
I love you. too.

19
00:01:09.970 --> 00:01:11.530
- I'm sorry?
- Who said that?

20
00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:12.470
Did you say. 'too'?

21
00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:16.510
No. I just said'you' twice. I said "I love you. you". Isn't that...

22
00:01:16.840 --> 00:01:18.510
What I said? Oh. god. Ooh!

23
00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:21.110
Daniel. Table 3.

24
00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:27.600
Ah! It's so—

25
00:01:32.920 --> 00:01:36.260
I'm so sorry to interrupt. but Piper's kind of got a bit of a. um...

26
00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:38.930
a power problem. She kinda needs some more.

27
00:01:39.090 --> 00:01:40.800
Why doesn't she just call the power company?

28
00:01:41.030 --> 00:01:43.970
Tried. and... the line is busy.

29
00:01:44.130 --> 00:01:47.500
So if you could come. like. right now. she'd really love it.

30
00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:51.010
Oh! Oh. please don't use that word. Please don't use that word.

31
00:01:51.110 --> 00:01:54.610
Ok. All right. So. I should go. and we will. you know —

32
00:01:54.710 --> 00:01:55.210
Talk.

33
00:01:55.310 --> 00:01:57.480
Talk! Yeah!

34
00:01:58.450 --> 00:02:01.720
Oh! Oh. I'm sorry! I'm sorry.

35
00:02:03.380 --> 00:02:05.420
Sorry! Ok...

36
00:02:05.990 --> 00:02:11.290
Ooh! The stuffed shells. Great choice. Ok. Bye. everyone.

37
00:02:23.970 --> 00:02:25.040
Ok. let's vanquish this demon.

38
00:02:27.110 --> 00:02:29.310
Shh! Something beat us to the punch.

39
00:02:31.880 --> 00:02:32.980
Eew. What is it doing?

40
00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:34.780
Apparently eating the demon.

41
00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:43.290
Or storing it.

42
00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:48.930
What is it?

43
00:02:49.060 --> 00:02:51.570
I don't know. And I don't wanna find out. Let's get outta here.

44
00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:04.680
Paige. do something!

45
00:03:06.420 --> 00:03:07.650
Power lines!

46
00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:19.930
You ok?

47
00:03:20.060 --> 00:03:20.860
Peachy.

48
00:03:44.390 --> 00:03:45.350
Cute.

49
00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:38.130
I still can't believe we vanquished his mommy.

50
00:05:38.470 --> 00:05:41.870
Yeah. but we didn't know it was a mommy. and besides. mommy tried to kill us.

51
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:46.340
I know. Still. look at how cute he is. So adorable.

52
00:05:46.610 --> 00:05:49.550
Oh. except when he does that weird little thing with his tongue.

53
00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:51.980
I wonder why he looks so human.

54
00:05:52.110 --> 00:05:54.480
I don't know. But he won't for long.

55
00:05:55.120 --> 00:05:58.020
Ok. Wyatt's upstairs. so at least he's...

56
00:06:04.090 --> 00:06:05.090
safe.

57
00:06:05.530 --> 00:06:07.630
Don't worry about Wyatt. He's got his protective bubble.

58
00:06:07.730 --> 00:06:08.760
He'll use it if he needs it.

59
00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:11.500
Plus. it looks like he likes his new friend.

60
00:06:11.630 --> 00:06:14.140
That is not a friend. That's a demon.

61
00:06:14.240 --> 00:06:15.600
No. he's just a baby!

62
00:06:15.740 --> 00:06:18.240
'Scuse me. Were you at the same vanquish as me?

63
00:06:18.310 --> 00:06:20.780
Because it took all three of us to stop its mother.

64
00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:22.650
It doesn't mean he's gonna turn out that way.

65
00:06:22.750 --> 00:06:24.610
Paige. he doesn't have a choice. It's genetic.

66
00:06:24.710 --> 00:06:25.650
No. I don't think so.

67
00:06:25.750 --> 00:06:27.520
Okay. Maybe I'm a little biased because I am.

68
00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:31.690
in fact. adopted. but I really think there's something to the whole nurture versus nature thing and predicting

69
00:06:31.790 --> 00:06:36.490
how a kid is gonna turn out. you know. the classic environment versus biology argument.

70
00:06:36.590 --> 00:06:38.460
But this is not a child. It's a demon.

71
00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:43.000
Ok. Why don't you go over there and see if you can sense anything evil.

72
00:06:45.700 --> 00:06:46.500
All right.

73
00:06:53.710 --> 00:06:55.140
Nothing... good or evil.

74
00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:57.950
My point exactly! Clay to be molded.

75
00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:03.000
So you vanquished the demon?

76
00:07:03.100 --> 00:07:04.500
Yes... and no.

77
00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:09.990
Well. the good news is the demon you sent us after is. in fact. uh... gone.

78
00:07:10.090 --> 00:07:14.560
And the bad news is is whatever ate it... left us that.

79
00:07:19.400 --> 00:07:20.440
I think he likes you.

80
00:07:20.570 --> 00:07:21.870
I don't care. Vanquish it.

81
00:07:21.940 --> 00:07:22.540
Chris!

82
00:07:22.640 --> 00:07:23.840
I mean it. Now.

83
00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:26.610
No! We are not vanquishing a baby. What's wrong with you?

84
00:07:26.710 --> 00:07:29.310
I'm just concerned that this could be the future evil that gets to Wyatt.

85
00:07:29.410 --> 00:07:30.380
Don't be ridiculous.

86
00:07:30.480 --> 00:07:34.280
What? I'm being ridiculous? There's a demon in the playpen.

87
00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:38.390
I'll get it.

88
00:07:39.220 --> 00:07:41.760
Hey. if it's Jason. tell him I'm in the shower.

89
00:07:42.660 --> 00:07:44.590
Are you avoiding him?

90
00:07:44.990 --> 00:07:51.530
Uh... kind of. I. um... sort of told him that I loved him last night.

91
00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.770
Oh. And this is bad?

92
00:07:53.940 --> 00:08:02.240
No. Except I said."I love you. too." as if he said."I love you" first. which he didn't.

93
00:08:02.910 --> 00:08:07.120
So. wait... you told him that he loves you before he told you that he loves you?

94
00:08:08.150 --> 00:08:09.000
Yeah. that's not good.

95
00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:12.860
Yeah. I'll be lucky if he doesn't move to Hong Kong permanently now.

96
00:08:13.290 --> 00:08:15.590
I really thought I had my empath power under control.

97
00:08:15.960 --> 00:08:17.390
Forget that. What are you gonna do?

98
00:08:17.490 --> 00:08:18.630
What am I supposed to do?

99
00:08:18.730 --> 00:08:21.400
I mean. you tell a guy that you love them. and they bolt.

100
00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:22.800
It's just what they do.

101
00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:25.870
About the baby. I meant the baby. We gotta do something.

102
00:08:32.400 --> 00:08:33.380
Fast.

103
00:08:35.180 --> 00:08:37.710
I can't hear you. Darryl. Speak up.

104
00:08:38.450 --> 00:08:40.680
I know I never asked before. but I'm asking now.

105
00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:45.050
I need help on this one. Magical help.

106
00:08:45.190 --> 00:08:46.790
All right. What's going on?

107
00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:49.190
This stupid kid. I- I mean. he's got hostages.

108
00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:53.860
Only I know him - he wouldn't hurt anybody — but I'm running out of time to talk him down.

109
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.530
S. W. A. T. 's ready to move in. I don't want to lose him. Paige.

110
00:08:59.030 --> 00:09:00.370
All right.

111
00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:04.910
All right! I'm coming. Ok. Hold your horses.

112
00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:11.180
Where's Wyatt?

113
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:12.080
Where is he?

114
00:09:12.180 --> 00:09:13.620
Look. look. wait. Listen.

115
00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:14.680
Where's Wyatt?

116
00:09:14.850 --> 00:09:16.390
There he is!

117
00:09:17.290 --> 00:09:18.520
Look! Look!

118
00:09:19.420 --> 00:09:21.360
Where's Wyatt? Where's Wyatt?

119
00:09:21.520 --> 00:09:22.830
There he is!

120
00:09:23.990 --> 00:09:24.860
All right.

121
00:09:24.960 --> 00:09:26.860
I don't think distracting him is the answer.

122
00:09:26.960 --> 00:09:30.370
Wyatt. bad demon. Very bad demon.

123
00:09:32.170 --> 00:09:33.240
Hey. was that Jason?

124
00:09:33.340 --> 00:09:36.110
No. That was my raison d'etre.

125
00:09:36.610 --> 00:09:37.570
Pardon?

126
00:09:37.670 --> 00:09:41.640
That was Darryl. I've been wondering why the temp agency hasn't called. and now I know why.

127
00:09:41.740 --> 00:09:43.750
I needed to be free to help him.

128
00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:45.350
To do what?

129
00:09:45.480 --> 00:09:48.250
Well. to save an innocent. Why else would he have called?

130
00:09:48.350 --> 00:09:52.220
And. more importantly. why else would I have been the one to answer the phone?

131
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:54.390
'Cause you were the closest to it?

132
00:09:54.520 --> 00:09:58.360
No. Because it's my reason for being. Call me if you need help.

133
00:09:59.730 --> 00:10:01.260
What? — You're just gonna let her go?

134
00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:03.070
You're welcome to try and stop her.

135
00:10:03.470 --> 00:10:05.200
You know I should go talk to Jason.

136
00:10:05.500 --> 00:10:06.400
And her. too.

137
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:08.540
Wait. Stop. Where are you going?

138
00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:10.910
Are you slightly concerned that there's a demon in the house?

139
00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:17.050
Chris. this is a baby. ok? Relax. You call me if you need anything.

140
00:10:17.480 --> 00:10:18.550
Love you. too.

141
00:10:19.080 --> 00:10:19.650
Don't.

142
00:10:20.820 --> 00:10:21.650
Sorry.

143
00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:24.090
And you're okay with this? Them dumping this on your lap?

144
00:10:24.190 --> 00:10:25.590
Well. they don't seem too worried.

145
00:10:25.690 --> 00:10:31.260
Well. they should be. I need to figure out what kind of creature we're dealing with here.

146
00:11:34.420 --> 00:11:35.390
Hey. is he in?

147
00:11:35.520 --> 00:11:38.390
No. I mean. yes. he is. but he asked not to be disturbed.

148
00:11:38.760 --> 00:11:40.700
Yeah. but that can't possibly mean me.

149
00:11:40.830 --> 00:11:43.330
Actually. it specifically means you. Phoebe. Sorry.

150
00:11:43.470 --> 00:11:44.630
You guys have a fight?

151
00:11:44.900 --> 00:11:46.800
No. But we're about to.

152
00:11:49.640 --> 00:11:52.470
Listen. Jas- oh.

153
00:11:56.000 --> 00:11:57.710
Oh... I'm sorry.

154
00:11:57.800 --> 00:11:59.580
Phoebe. what are you doing?

155
00:11:59.680 --> 00:12:01.320
I didn't know you were in the middle of a meeting.

156
00:12:01.420 --> 00:12:03.890
Yeah. That's why the door was closed.

157
00:12:03.990 --> 00:12:08.090
Really? Because I was told the door was closed specifically for me.

158
00:12:09.690 --> 00:12:12.360
Vogliate scusarmi. Torno subito.

159
00:12:13.660 --> 00:12:15.130
I didn't know you spoke Italian.

160
00:12:15.230 --> 00:12:16.030
Outside.

161
00:12:17.070 --> 00:12:18.570
How come I didn't know you speak Italian?

162
00:12:20.670 --> 00:12:21.970
Is that what you came here to ask?

163
00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:27.180
No. No. of course not. I just wanted to talk about last night.

164
00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:32.350
Ok. fine. but can we do it later? I'm in the middle of a very important meeting right now.

165
00:12:32.450 --> 00:12:38.420
Of course. Yeah. I'm sorry about that. So how about tonight?

166
00:12:38.520 --> 00:12:45.260
Tonight. Tonight's not good. I'm flying to Rome.

167
00:12:49.400 --> 00:12:50.430
Wait. What?

168
00:12:50.770 --> 00:12:53.540
I was meaning to tell you. It just came up.

169
00:12:54.340 --> 00:12:57.870
Really? When? Right after I told you I loved you?

170
00:12:57.970 --> 00:12:58.540
Aw. come on!

171
00:12:58.610 --> 00:13:02.340
I've heard of guys running when they hear the "L" word. but running allthe way to Italy?

172
00:13:02.440 --> 00:13:03.710
That's gotta be some kind of new record!

173
00:13:03.810 --> 00:13:05.180
Would you keep your voice down. please?

174
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.950
It's got nothing to do with that. and you know it.

175
00:13:09.050 --> 00:13:12.390
That's a crock. We both know how you really feel about me.

176
00:13:12.520 --> 00:13:15.620
The only difference is I'm the only one who's not afraid of it. Ciao!

177
00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:24.130
Vicious demons with supernatural strength and venomous claws.

178
00:13:24.230 --> 00:13:28.240
manticores communicate with high- pitched cries and tend to travel in "packs."

179
00:13:29.640 --> 00:13:33.680
Great. I say we get rid of the little brat before the pack comes looking for him.

180
00:13:33.810 --> 00:13:37.410
Ok. Fine. What do you suggest we do with him. call social services?

181
00:13:37.510 --> 00:13:39.280
No. I suggest you vanquish it.

182
00:13:39.620 --> 00:13:43.450
Chris. I'm a mother. I can't go around vanquishing babies. no matter how evil they are.

183
00:13:43.750 --> 00:13:46.260
It's not how evil he is. It's how evil he's gonna be.

184
00:13:46.420 --> 00:13:48.390
You gotta stop looking at him like he's a little baby

185
00:13:48.490 --> 00:13:51.930
and start looking at him like he's an unstoppable killing machine. because that's what he is.

186
00:13:52.030 --> 00:13:53.430
I realize that. but still —

187
00:13:53.530 --> 00:13:56.670
— But still nothing. You're supposed to protect the innocents. right?

188
00:13:56.800 --> 00:14:00.870
Think of all the future innocents you can save by vanquishing him right now.

189
00:14:00.970 --> 00:14:02.170
Don't you think I know that?

190
00:14:02.270 --> 00:14:06.280
I'm scared to death of what he could possibly to do Wyatt. but I can't even separate them.

191
00:14:06.410 --> 00:14:08.610
Piper. there's one thing you can do. and you know it.

192
00:14:08.740 --> 00:14:11.350
And you'd better do it fast before any other manticores show up.

193
00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:13.480
There's no known vanquishing potion.

194
00:14:16.950 --> 00:14:19.260
I just... can't do it.

195
00:14:20.620 --> 00:14:24.790
Ok. Well. if you won't listen to me. maybe you'll listen to Leo.

196
00:15:20.600 --> 00:15:22.750
We're in position. Lieutenant. We've got a clean shot.

197
00:15:25.960 --> 00:15:28.360
Darryl! Darryl! Over here!

198
00:15:28.460 --> 00:15:30.000
Stand by. It's ok. Let her through.

199
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:34.760
What took you so long?

200
00:15:34.860 --> 00:15:38.030
I would have orbed here. but that could have been more magic than you had in mind.

201
00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:39.970
I'm not sure what you could have done anyway.

202
00:15:40.070 --> 00:15:43.070
He's not letting any of the hostages go. and S. W. A. T. 'S ready to move in.

203
00:15:43.340 --> 00:15:45.980
Forget that. I'm not giving up. This is my raison d'etre.

204
00:15:46.740 --> 00:15:47.580
Excuse me?

205
00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:52.080
Listen. I came to help. That's exactly what I'm gonna do. so what do you need?

206
00:15:53.020 --> 00:15:57.090
I don't know. If I could just talk to the kid... without getting shot.

207
00:15:59.120 --> 00:16:00.990
I think I have the perfect spell for this.

208
00:16:01.260 --> 00:16:04.190
Whoa. whoa. Spell? What spell?

209
00:16:04.560 --> 00:16:06.130
Just go with me. ok?

210
00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.360
Blessed with powers from my destiny.

211
00:16:08.460 --> 00:16:10.600
I bless this hero with invincibility.

212
00:16:14.900 --> 00:16:15.970
How do you feel?

213
00:16:16.170 --> 00:16:18.610
It feels... it feels good.

214
00:16:19.780 --> 00:16:21.280
All right. Go get him. tough guy.

215
00:16:33.700 --> 00:16:35.300
Lieutenant. what are you doing?

216
00:16:39.500 --> 00:16:43.400
Hey. turn around! Get outta here! I swear to god. man. I'll shoot!

217
00:16:43.530 --> 00:16:45.630
I'll shoot you. man! I swear to god I'll do it!

218
00:16:46.170 --> 00:16:48.400
Put your gun down. son. I just wanna talk.

219
00:17:02.720 --> 00:17:04.690
That's ok. Hold your fire.

220
00:17:05.250 --> 00:17:06.460
I'm goin' in.

221
00:17:19.030 --> 00:17:20.540
Leo. I have been looking everywhere for you.

222
00:17:22.840 --> 00:17:24.110
What are you doing up here?

223
00:17:24.670 --> 00:17:25.880
Communing with the others.

224
00:17:28.780 --> 00:17:29.780
Can anyone see us?

225
00:17:29.880 --> 00:17:33.650
Not me... but you look like a lunatic standing up here talking to yourself.

226
00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:36.590
What do you want?

227
00:17:36.650 --> 00:17:38.110
It's about Piper.

228
00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:39.090
Is she all right?

229
00:17:39.290 --> 00:17:42.730
Yes. she's fine. Don't worry. It's Wyatt I'm worried about.

230
00:17:43.160 --> 00:17:43.930
Why. what happened?

231
00:17:44.030 --> 00:17:47.960
Nothing yet. Just out of curiosity. on vanquishing demon babies?

232
00:17:49.230 --> 00:17:49.970
Why?

233
00:17:50.130 --> 00:17:52.900
No reason. There's just one playing with Wyatt in his playpen as we speak.

234
00:17:55.740 --> 00:17:58.510
Ok. listen to me. You will not orb down to your little friend.

235
00:17:58.770 --> 00:18:01.410
Do you understand me? No orbing.

236
00:18:07.820 --> 00:18:08.720
I give up.

237
00:18:13.390 --> 00:18:17.860
Whoo! I have had it with men. They are incorrigible.

238
00:18:18.030 --> 00:18:20.100
Well. let me tell you. little boys are not much better.

239
00:18:20.300 --> 00:18:23.500
I could understand running if he didn't love me back. you know?

240
00:18:23.630 --> 00:18:25.670
Fight or flight. It's the nature of the beast.

241
00:18:25.770 --> 00:18:26.740
Speaking of that —

242
00:18:26.840 --> 00:18:29.410
But he does love me. I know. I felt it. you know?

243
00:18:29.470 --> 00:18:31.810
So what's the big deal? Why is he running?

244
00:18:31.940 --> 00:18:33.480
Well. if it makes you feel any better.

245
00:18:33.580 --> 00:18:36.410
you probably won't be alive much longer to worry about it.

246
00:18:36.550 --> 00:18:39.250
Thank you. yes. That makes me feel so much better.

247
00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:41.220
I'm just saying. if this doesn't work.

248
00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:44.820
we may not be able to vanquish the manticores when they come to pick up their little one.

249
00:18:45.090 --> 00:18:46.290
Oh. you figured out what they are?

250
00:18:46.390 --> 00:18:48.660
Yeah. And it's not good. believe me.

251
00:18:48.790 --> 00:18:50.490
So maybe Chris was right.

252
00:18:50.630 --> 00:18:54.100
Yeah. I know. but... I can't.

253
00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:56.500
Piper. you said it yourself. He was born evil.

254
00:18:56.600 --> 00:19:02.070
I know. And I still believe that. I do. But something just doesn't add up about him.

255
00:19:02.140 --> 00:19:04.240
Why isn't Wyatt using his protective shield?

256
00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:06.080
Why doesn't Wyatt think he's evil?

257
00:19:06.840 --> 00:19:08.910
Well. we gotta keep Wyatt away from him.

258
00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:10.450
Phoebe. wait -

259
00:19:10.510 --> 00:19:13.020
You stay away from my nephew. ok?

260
00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:15.380
And don't shimmer after him either. or I'll bind your powers.

261
00:19:17.290 --> 00:19:18.590
Phoebe. hurry! Put him back down.

262
00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:21.090
What? Ok...

263
00:19:21.920 --> 00:19:22.790
Why?

264
00:19:23.930 --> 00:19:25.530
That's why.

265
00:19:33.770 --> 00:19:38.210
Hey! You get away from my kid!

266
00:20:00.530 --> 00:20:03.370
I feel really bad that I wasn't there to help you earlier.

267
00:20:03.370 --> 00:20:05.670
Oh. I don't think you could've helped even if you were there.

268
00:20:05.770 --> 00:20:09.710
Thanks. That thing was just as powerful as the manticore.

269
00:20:09.970 --> 00:20:11.470
Are you sure it wasn't a manticore?

270
00:20:11.570 --> 00:20:15.440
Yeah. I'm positive. It was more. I don't know. like. beast- like.

271
00:20:15.980 --> 00:20:17.550
What do you think it wanted with the baby?

272
00:20:17.650 --> 00:20:22.050
I don't know. but I think it's really weird that is showed up right after the baby started crying.

273
00:20:22.150 --> 00:20:23.650
You know. as if it could hear him.

274
00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:26.590
Maybe we can get the baby to cry again and lure The Beast here.

275
00:20:26.690 --> 00:20:28.460
and torture him into coughing up Piper.

276
00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:30.260
It's a great idea. but we don't have a potion yet.

277
00:20:31.390 --> 00:20:33.360
I can't find Piper anywhere.

278
00:20:34.460 --> 00:20:37.270
Ok. let me get started on the potion.

279
00:20:37.400 --> 00:20:41.570
The good news is if he wanted to kill Piper by now. he probably would have.

280
00:20:41.770 --> 00:20:46.080
And undoubtedly he's holding her hostage somewhere. probably magically cloaked.

281
00:20:46.280 --> 00:20:50.650
And I think he's gonna use her as leverage to get that baby. just you watch.

282
00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:53.820
Since when did you become an expert on hostage situations?

283
00:20:54.220 --> 00:20:55.180
About an hour ago.

284
00:20:59.020 --> 00:21:02.460
Shh. shh. Keep it down. Don't wake the baby. Trust me.

285
00:21:02.660 --> 00:21:03.660
Where's Piper?

286
00:21:03.790 --> 00:21:05.090
That's a really good question.

287
00:21:05.230 --> 00:21:06.160
Wait. she's missing?

288
00:21:06.260 --> 00:21:07.230
Did the manticores take her?

289
00:21:07.330 --> 00:21:09.160
No. some other creature that wanted the baby.

290
00:21:09.300 --> 00:21:10.300
Damn it. you should have listened to me.

291
00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:11.800
You should have vanquished him when you had the chance.

292
00:21:11.900 --> 00:21:15.040
Well. it's good that we didn't because we're gonna need the baby to get Piper back.

293
00:21:15.300 --> 00:21:16.810
You guys. shh. Keep your voices down.

294
00:21:17.010 --> 00:21:19.640
I am not convinced that that baby is inherently evil.

295
00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:22.240
which means he's probably not even responsible for any of this.

296
00:21:22.340 --> 00:21:23.810
Oh. come on! Will you please talk to her?

297
00:21:24.610 --> 00:21:30.050
Not everyone is born morally neutral. especially not demons. They're predisposed to evil.

298
00:21:30.190 --> 00:21:33.120
Predisposed. yeah. but it doesn't mean they can't be raised to overcome it.

299
00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:37.060
You can't predict whether a kid is gonna be good or evil based on his genetics.

300
00:21:37.160 --> 00:21:39.530
Paige. we're not talking about kids. We're talking about demons.

301
00:21:39.660 --> 00:21:44.630
No. we are talking about a demon kid who so far has played nothing but nice with Wyatt.

302
00:21:44.770 --> 00:21:46.340
Ok. you guys. this is all irrelevant.

303
00:21:46.440 --> 00:21:49.470
We need the baby to find Piper. so let's just focus on that. shall we?

304
00:21:50.040 --> 00:21:53.410
She's right. Although I think I should take Wyatt just to be on the safe side.

305
00:21:53.840 --> 00:21:55.140
What if the other baby wakes up?

306
00:21:55.280 --> 00:21:57.080
They won't be able to follow me where I'm going.

307
00:22:00.120 --> 00:22:04.490
It's gonna scream bloody murder and call half the manticores in the city to come save it.

308
00:22:04.590 --> 00:22:05.720
Maybe The Beast. too.

309
00:22:05.820 --> 00:22:09.960
We have to be prepared. Ok. Go. just quietly.

310
00:22:14.060 --> 00:22:15.730
Let's get started on that potion.

311
00:22:38.920 --> 00:22:41.060
Hello? Who's there?

312
00:22:42.120 --> 00:22:43.330
I want the child.

313
00:22:44.330 --> 00:22:45.230
Who are you?

314
00:22:45.360 --> 00:22:46.500
I want the child!

315
00:22:46.730 --> 00:22:48.930
Yeah. I heard you the first time.

316
00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:57.410
Look. if you're trying to scare me. it's not gonna work'cause I've seen worse. Really.

317
00:22:57.810 --> 00:23:03.650
I doubt it. I don't want to hurt you. but I will if you don't do as I ask.

318
00:23:03.950 --> 00:23:08.480
Who are you kidding? You need me. otherwise I'd be dead already.

319
00:23:08.850 --> 00:23:10.690
Don't mock me!

320
00:23:10.920 --> 00:23:13.920
Ok. easy. easy. Sorry.

321
00:23:16.530 --> 00:23:22.060
You're not a manticore. are you? So why do you want the kid anyway?

322
00:23:23.170 --> 00:23:24.470
That's not your concern.

323
00:23:24.570 --> 00:23:29.310
Well. it is if you want my help. I'm not just gonna serve him up to you as a snack.

324
00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:35.080
That's not why I want him. How'd you get him away from his mother anyway?

325
00:23:35.680 --> 00:23:37.080
We vanquished her.

326
00:23:40.050 --> 00:23:41.950
You have no idea what you've done.

327
00:23:42.120 --> 00:23:45.960
We got a baby away from a demon. and I'm not gonna give him up to another one.

328
00:23:46.120 --> 00:23:47.360
Then you'll die!

329
00:23:47.490 --> 00:23:48.860
The hell I will.

330
00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:08.440
Any sign of the lieutenant?

331
00:24:08.640 --> 00:24:09.310
Negative.

332
00:24:09.480 --> 00:24:12.980
All right. we'll give him 5 more minutes to talk him out. then we'll—

333
00:24:14.250 --> 00:24:15.820
Hold your fire. Hold your fire.

334
00:24:19.420 --> 00:24:22.090
Don't' shoot! They're hostages!

335
00:24:39.800 --> 00:24:44.000
No sweat! I got it! This lieutenant's on the job. kicking butt. taking names.

336
00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:46.820
yeah. that's right! That's me! I got it! No sweat!

337
00:24:46.900 --> 00:24:49.000
Yeah. gimme 5. Gimme 5. Gimme some skin.

338
00:24:49.400 --> 00:24:50.900
How you doin'? You lookin' good. Tim.

339
00:24:55.550 --> 00:24:56.600
How'd you do it. man?

340
00:24:56.700 --> 00:24:58.800
How did those bullets bounce right off of your chest like that?

341
00:24:58.900 --> 00:25:00.500
'Cause I'm a bad- ass. that's why. punk.

342
00:25:02.500 --> 00:25:04.000
What the hell was that?

343
00:25:04.670 --> 00:25:05.370
Shut up.

344
00:25:11.440 --> 00:25:13.110
What the hell are you. man?

345
00:25:45.780 --> 00:25:49.350
Last chance. Help me get the child or die.

346
00:25:51.310 --> 00:25:53.280
What are you doing with this?

347
00:25:57.500 --> 00:25:59.890
What is the matter with you? Do you have a death wish?

348
00:26:02.020 --> 00:26:05.590
I've come too far. I've gone through too much to lose him now.

349
00:26:05.930 --> 00:26:07.630
Don't make me kill you!

350
00:26:08.600 --> 00:26:10.430
Why don't you just do it? What are you waiting for?

351
00:26:12.170 --> 00:26:13.270
Get it over with!

352
00:26:16.070 --> 00:26:19.640
I can do worse than kill you. I can keep you here.

353
00:26:20.180 --> 00:26:24.580
You'll never see your child again. Think about it.

354
00:26:32.690 --> 00:26:34.590
Well. can't think of anything else to add.

355
00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:36.760
It's the most powerful potion we've ever made.

356
00:26:36.890 --> 00:26:39.760
I agree. I guess it's time to wake up the baby?

357
00:26:45.800 --> 00:26:46.340
Hello?

358
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:47.300
Hey. it's me.

359
00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:48.870
Oh. hey. Jason.

360
00:26:50.070 --> 00:26:53.680
I. uh... I didn't want to leave like this.

361
00:26:53.780 --> 00:26:56.610
Uh. I can't really talk right now. I'm kind of busy.

362
00:26:56.750 --> 00:26:58.910
Oh. really? Come on. Phoebe.

363
00:26:58.980 --> 00:27:01.420
Why do you always have to make things so difficult?

364
00:27:01.580 --> 00:27:03.520
Oh. I make things so difficult?

365
00:27:03.690 --> 00:27:05.420
And how exactly do I do that?

366
00:27:05.520 --> 00:27:09.960
By being honest with my feelings and by making you be honest with yours?

367
00:27:10.090 --> 00:27:11.360
You know it's not that simple.

368
00:27:14.460 --> 00:27:15.970
Ok. I really have to go now.

369
00:27:16.030 --> 00:27:17.530
- Phoebe. wait.
- Have a good flight.

370
00:27:19.130 --> 00:27:19.970
Toss me a vial.

371
00:27:29.110 --> 00:27:30.010
Paige. you ok?

372
00:28:06.550 --> 00:28:07.620
Phoebe. get the vial!

373
00:28:19.160 --> 00:28:20.560
So much for our leverage.

374
00:29:00.700 --> 00:29:04.810
Shh. You're ok. It's all right. You're home now.

375
00:29:20.520 --> 00:29:22.360
This had better work.

376
00:29:22.690 --> 00:29:23.630
Oh. it will.

377
00:29:27.260 --> 00:29:29.430
We just got back from talking to The Elders. and they're in agreement.

378
00:29:29.530 --> 00:29:31.400
If we can't return the baby safely to the manticores...

379
00:29:31.500 --> 00:29:32.570
we'll vanquish him.

380
00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:35.340
Talk about your moot points. people.

381
00:29:36.040 --> 00:29:36.870
What's that supposed to mean?

382
00:29:37.040 --> 00:29:38.570
Well. do you notice anything missing?

383
00:29:41.810 --> 00:29:42.580
The baby?

384
00:29:43.050 --> 00:29:43.880
What happened?

385
00:29:44.210 --> 00:29:47.050
The Beast took him... right after the manticores kicked our asses.

386
00:29:47.480 --> 00:29:48.750
This is all Jason's fault.

387
00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:50.220
How's that?

388
00:29:50.420 --> 00:29:51.920
Oh. you're a guy. You wouldn't get it.

389
00:29:52.050 --> 00:29:54.720
Wait. How are we supposed to get back Piper if we don't have a baby?

390
00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:57.590
Well. we're gonna try to have another little get- together with the manticores.

391
00:29:57.730 --> 00:29:59.400
See if we can't strike some sort of deal.

392
00:29:59.530 --> 00:30:01.600
If we can join forces with them to kill the beast.

393
00:30:01.700 --> 00:30:02.900
then they can get their baby back.

394
00:30:03.030 --> 00:30:04.400
And we get our sister back.

395
00:30:04.630 --> 00:30:06.670
And what if they don't want to join forces?

396
00:30:06.800 --> 00:30:10.270
Well. then we hope we have enough of these fancy little things to go around.

397
00:30:10.610 --> 00:30:12.110
No. No way. It's too risky.

398
00:30:12.370 --> 00:30:15.340
Well. blood is thicker than water.

399
00:30:22.990 --> 00:30:24.420
Well. quit moving around so much.

400
00:30:24.550 --> 00:30:25.920
You're just making this more difficult.

401
00:30:26.920 --> 00:30:28.020
Just leave me alone.

402
00:30:28.890 --> 00:30:32.090
Why? So you can die? Hey. it's your choice.

403
00:30:32.190 --> 00:30:34.260
I'm just saying if we can't stop this bleeding—

404
00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:36.000
Fine. Whatever. Just hurry up.

405
00:30:36.730 --> 00:30:40.870
You're welcome. Who did this to you?

406
00:30:41.700 --> 00:30:42.810
Your sisters.

407
00:30:43.270 --> 00:30:44.970
Oh. Sorry.

408
00:30:45.710 --> 00:30:49.180
Actually. if they used the potion I think they did. you're lucky to be alive.

409
00:30:49.280 --> 00:30:50.650
You should have been blown to pieces.

410
00:30:50.780 --> 00:30:51.680
How do you know?

411
00:30:51.780 --> 00:30:53.850
Well. 'cause I made it.

412
00:30:55.780 --> 00:30:58.320
Oh. come on. Show a little spine. What kind of demon are you?

413
00:30:58.450 --> 00:30:59.560
I'm not a demon.

414
00:31:00.960 --> 00:31:06.000
Then what are you? I saw a picture of a man in the bedroom.

415
00:31:07.330 --> 00:31:09.930
Oh. come on. I've been around a lot of demons.

416
00:31:10.100 --> 00:31:13.670
and they don't usually live in neighborhoods right out of Home & Garden.

417
00:31:13.840 --> 00:31:15.270
Is that why you're helping me?

418
00:31:15.870 --> 00:31:18.570
You think this is some sort of hideous curse or something?

419
00:31:19.140 --> 00:31:20.580
Yeah. basically.

420
00:31:22.710 --> 00:31:25.250
Well. then go. I don't need your pity.

421
00:31:25.410 --> 00:31:27.720
That's no what happened. and that's not who I am.

422
00:31:28.580 --> 00:31:33.120
Not anymore. anyway. Just leave us. Go.

423
00:31:33.520 --> 00:31:39.800
Us? You mean you and your... son? What happened?

424
00:31:43.830 --> 00:31:48.270
Manticores mate with humans to create hybrids so they can blend in.

425
00:31:48.400 --> 00:31:53.010
Hide in plain sight. They kill their mates after conception. but I got away.

426
00:31:54.380 --> 00:31:57.180
Ever since. all I could think about was saving my son.

427
00:31:57.680 --> 00:32:00.250
So he wouldn't have to be raised like one of them.

428
00:32:01.050 --> 00:32:06.160
The only chance I had to do that was... to turn myself into this. to become powerful.

429
00:32:06.590 --> 00:32:08.720
But. um. how?

430
00:32:08.960 --> 00:32:13.500
I just started mixing potions... using whatever I could steal from them.

431
00:32:13.960 --> 00:32:16.700
I didn't know what I was doing. but I didn't care.

432
00:32:16.800 --> 00:32:20.070
All I cared about was finding a way to fight them... to find him.

433
00:32:22.500 --> 00:32:26.980
I didn't care what would happen to me. I just wanted my son.

434
00:32:32.180 --> 00:32:33.980
You know they're gonna try and take him back.

435
00:32:35.550 --> 00:32:36.520
I know.

436
00:32:37.690 --> 00:32:40.720
So let's get you fixed up so we can fight them together.

437
00:33:03.810 --> 00:33:04.910
Sorry to interrupt.

438
00:33:06.680 --> 00:33:08.720
Ah- ah- ah! I wouldn't do that if I were you.

439
00:33:12.620 --> 00:33:14.320
Do you think we have enough potion?

440
00:33:15.620 --> 00:33:18.030
So... who wants to go hunting with us?

441
00:33:25.200 --> 00:33:26.600
This is gonna be a little cold.

442
00:33:34.180 --> 00:33:37.680
The bleeding's not stopping. You should come home with me. and we can do more there.

443
00:33:38.750 --> 00:33:39.720
No. I can't.

444
00:33:40.350 --> 00:33:41.720
If you're worried about my sisters —

445
00:33:41.880 --> 00:33:45.890
It's not your sisters I'm worried about. It's the manticores.

446
00:33:46.020 --> 00:33:49.190
They'll be looking for me there. They'll be looking for him there.

447
00:33:49.290 --> 00:33:52.660
But you don't understand. We have somebody who can heal you once we turn you back into—

448
00:33:52.760 --> 00:33:58.530
You can't turn me back. No one can. Not unless I die.

449
00:34:00.370 --> 00:34:02.710
So how were you planning on raising your son?

450
00:34:02.840 --> 00:34:07.210
I wasn't. I figured I'd find someone... after.

451
00:34:08.110 --> 00:34:12.750
All I cared about was saving him. That's exactly what I'm gonna keep on doing.

452
00:34:14.950 --> 00:34:19.020
You can't run forever. you know. Not for long. Not with that.

453
00:34:19.590 --> 00:34:21.460
And who's gonna save him when you're dead?

454
00:34:23.130 --> 00:34:25.260
You have a way with words. you know that?

455
00:34:25.790 --> 00:34:26.960
I ad- lib a lot.

456
00:34:30.970 --> 00:34:31.930
Piper. duck!

457
00:34:34.170 --> 00:34:35.240
What are you doing?

458
00:34:38.500 --> 00:34:39.700
Let's get her out of here.

459
00:34:39.750 --> 00:34:40.700
No! Wait!

460
00:34:47.950 --> 00:34:49.120
What the hell are you doing?

461
00:34:49.220 --> 00:34:50.120
Saving your life.

462
00:34:50.220 --> 00:34:52.590
No. no. no. You don't understand. We have to go back. Hurry.

463
00:35:23.500 --> 00:35:24.750
Leo. we need you!

464
00:35:27.160 --> 00:35:28.520
Hurry. He's dying.

465
00:35:28.820 --> 00:35:29.630
Who is he?

466
00:35:29.790 --> 00:35:31.730
The Beast. Heal. Heal. Hurry.

467
00:35:32.130 --> 00:35:33.230
Where's the baby?

468
00:35:33.330 --> 00:35:34.260
Manticores have him.

469
00:35:34.360 --> 00:35:35.600
Oh. so the plan worked.

470
00:35:35.830 --> 00:35:37.100
Yeah. A little too well.

471
00:35:37.270 --> 00:35:39.100
And now we just have to get the baby back.

472
00:35:39.100 --> 00:35:39.840
What?

473
00:35:41.800 --> 00:35:43.770
Paige. will you go fill up some potion vials. please?

474
00:35:43.940 --> 00:35:44.510
Yeah.

475
00:35:44.610 --> 00:35:45.410
Lots of'em.

476
00:35:45.540 --> 00:35:46.640
Hold up. are you serious?

477
00:35:46.740 --> 00:35:49.650
You finally get rid of the demon child and now you want to risk your lives trying to get it back?

478
00:35:49.980 --> 00:35:51.310
He's not a demon child.

479
00:35:52.550 --> 00:35:53.780
That's my son.

480
00:35:54.450 --> 00:35:55.850
How are you feeling? Are you all right?

481
00:35:56.490 --> 00:35:58.020
I can't believe I'm human again.

482
00:35:58.250 --> 00:35:59.790
Aren't you glad you didn't kill me now?

483
00:36:00.120 --> 00:36:01.890
Not funny. I don't think that's funny.

484
00:36:02.020 --> 00:36:02.590
Agreed.

485
00:36:02.690 --> 00:36:05.360
Oh. what? Are you two on. like. the same team now?

486
00:36:07.300 --> 00:36:09.430
We're gonna get your baby back. I promise.

487
00:36:10.130 --> 00:36:11.270
Do we not have a say in this?

488
00:36:11.400 --> 00:36:12.600
No. we don't.

489
00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:17.500
One thing you gotta learn about being their Whitelighter is once they make up their mind. that's it.

490
00:36:17.500 --> 00:36:19.580
Besides. I'm a father first.

491
00:36:20.980 --> 00:36:25.050
So we're gonna have to separate the baby before we attack. You know that. right?

492
00:36:25.150 --> 00:36:25.750
Why?

493
00:36:25.780 --> 00:36:27.880
Well. because the potion vanquishes manticores.

494
00:36:28.020 --> 00:36:30.120
And... your son is half manticore.

495
00:36:44.030 --> 00:36:44.730
See him?

496
00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:47.340
Let's just hope he sees you before they see us.

497
00:36:47.700 --> 00:36:49.000
Should I just orb the baby to us?

498
00:36:49.470 --> 00:36:53.080
No. He'll probably just shimmer back. and then we'll be in trouble. but this is gonna work.

499
00:36:54.110 --> 00:36:54.710
Hurry. Hurry.

500
00:37:03.950 --> 00:37:05.220
You can do it. Come on. Come on.

501
00:37:07.220 --> 00:37:08.090
Peekaboo!

502
00:37:16.070 --> 00:37:17.570
Come on. You can do it.

503
00:37:40.790 --> 00:37:42.730
You're ok. Hi!

504
00:37:45.800 --> 00:37:46.800
Good job!

505
00:37:48.330 --> 00:37:51.000
So much for nature being more important than nurture.

506
00:38:29.740 --> 00:38:31.170
Here are some clothes and a stroller.

507
00:38:32.470 --> 00:38:33.380
Sure you don't mind?

508
00:38:33.640 --> 00:38:36.150
No. not at all. Wyatt has outgrown it all.

509
00:38:36.250 --> 00:38:39.850
and I don't see myself having more kids anytime soon. so enjoy.

510
00:38:40.220 --> 00:38:43.620
Thanks... uh. for everything.

511
00:38:44.050 --> 00:38:46.860
I just — I wish there was something I could do for you.

512
00:38:46.960 --> 00:38:49.230
Well. you could tell us your name.

513
00:38:49.960 --> 00:38:50.660
Sorry?

514
00:38:50.760 --> 00:38:53.360
I mean. unless you prefer being called "The Beast"?"

515
00:38:54.560 --> 00:38:56.970
Derek. My name's Derek.

516
00:38:57.630 --> 00:38:58.970
It's nice to meet you. Derek.

517
00:39:00.470 --> 00:39:01.770
What's his name?

518
00:39:01.970 --> 00:39:06.180
I— I never gave him one. Actually. I never — I never had the chance.

519
00:39:06.640 --> 00:39:07.810
Well. now you do.

520
00:39:09.910 --> 00:39:13.680
Well. I guess I should be going. That is if I can pry him away from Wyatt.

521
00:39:14.120 --> 00:39:15.350
Yeah. Good luck.

522
00:39:20.490 --> 00:39:21.590
That is cute.

523
00:39:22.690 --> 00:39:23.330
I'll get it.

524
00:39:25.660 --> 00:39:27.900
Uh. you know. if you ever need us to bind his powers...

525
00:39:28.300 --> 00:39:31.400
No. I mean. thanks. That's really sweet. but it's not necessary.

526
00:39:31.670 --> 00:39:35.300
He's a good boy. so... it's just up to me to make sure he stays that way.

527
00:39:36.140 --> 00:39:38.210
In that case. he's in good hands.

528
00:39:41.440 --> 00:39:42.210
Well. take care.

529
00:39:43.880 --> 00:39:44.710
You. too.

530
00:39:54.320 --> 00:39:55.720
What? What'd you do?

531
00:39:57.130 --> 00:40:00.400
I kinda forgot to reverse the spell I put on Darryl.

532
00:40:48.000 --> 00:40:50.950
What are you doing here? I— I thought you were on a plane.

533
00:40:52.250 --> 00:40:56.090
I canceled the flight. I mean. it is my plane.

534
00:40:58.050 --> 00:40:59.120
What about the winery?

535
00:40:59.720 --> 00:41:00.860
It'll be there in the morning.

536
00:41:02.560 --> 00:41:06.800
I. uh. just wasn't sure whether you would be.

537
00:41:07.160 --> 00:41:08.530
I didn't want to take the risk.

538
00:41:08.860 --> 00:41:09.400
Really?

539
00:41:09.770 --> 00:41:10.200
Really.

540
00:41:11.870 --> 00:41:16.640
You were right. I was — I was running. but not for the reasons that you think.

541
00:41:16.740 --> 00:41:20.680
I am not afraid of how I feel about you. It doesn't scare me one bit.

542
00:41:21.440 --> 00:41:22.710
Then why?

543
00:41:23.350 --> 00:41:28.550
It's... a little unnerving to have somebody tell you how you feel all the time...

544
00:41:29.120 --> 00:41:30.490
before you know it yourself.

545
00:41:31.390 --> 00:41:34.420
I know. I'm sorry.

546
00:41:34.560 --> 00:41:37.230
You do that a lot. too. You're very intuitive.

547
00:41:37.890 --> 00:41:42.800
It's. uh. it's pretty amazing. actually. It's a real gift.

548
00:41:43.670 --> 00:41:46.440
Yeah. well. sometimes it can be a curse. too.

549
00:41:46.970 --> 00:41:47.900
Tell me about it.

550
00:41:51.100 --> 00:42:00.580
Look. all I'm saying is that I'd like to be able to express my if that's all right with you?

551
00:42:01.580 --> 00:42:03.090
It's perfectly ok.

552
00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:03.590
Good.

553
00:42:08.260 --> 00:42:14.300
So... while we're on the subject... how do you feel about me?

554
00:42:17.170 --> 00:42:19.130
I love you. too.

555
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:32.000
Synchro: Greatouille
